## VOCABULARY GAPS FOUND:

# GAP 1: "think" (verb) - "thi" already means "thing"
# Need: new 3-letter word for the act of thinking
# Suggestion: "cog" (cognition), "pon" (ponder), "rea" (reason)?

# GAP 2: "reason" (verb) vs "reason" (noun/cause)
# "rea" could mean "read" OR "reason" - ambiguous
# Need: distinct words for "read text" vs "think logically"

# GAP 3: "want" vs "need" - both very primitive concepts
# wan: des to hav or do
# nee: mus hav to liv or fun
