## STOPPING POINT: Circular Dependency Detected

# Cannot proceed without resolving fundamental gaps:
# 1. No word for "think" (verb) - "thi" is "thing"
# 2. Cannot define "person" without "think"
# 3. Cannot define abstract values (good, bad, true, false) without circular logic
# 4. Cannot define mental states (want, need, believe, hope) at this primitive level
# 5. Modal verbs (can, must, should) require undefined concepts (ability, obligation)

# BOOTSTRAP PARADOX IDENTIFIED:
# To define complex concepts, you need simpler concepts
# But the "simpler" concepts often require the complex ones!
# Example: "understand" requires "know", but "know" requires "understand"

